Kobe rubber futures mixed in after - hours trade . Kobe rubber futures were mixed in extremely thin after - hours trade on Monday , as the market suffered from a lack of fresh incentives , traders said . Prices ranged from 0 . 5 yen per kg lower to 0 . 3 yen firmer than the day ' s close . Benchmark June was flat at 145 . 6 yen . Volume was 2 , 886 lots . During the day , prices drifted sideways in directionless trade . " Private investors ' interest was more in other commodity futures such as grain . In addition , a seasonal rise in rubber output in producing countries thinned fresh buying interest here , " one trader said . - - Tokyo Commodity Desk 
